Class TestAdmissionControllerSuccess

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.upmc.components.cvm.AbstractCVM

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    fr.upmc.components.cvm.ComponentVirtualMachineI

    public class TestAdmissionControllerSuccess
extends fr.upmc.components.cvm.AbstractCVM
    This class shows a test of one hosting two ApplicationContainer In this case we use 2 Computer in our data center means that we can allocate 4 Processor with 2 Cores or we can say that the ApplicationVM reserve 4 cores to execute the received requests. The test will succeed because there are available resources for 2 ApplicationConatiner Test : 2 Computer 2 * 2 Processors 8 Cores ( 4 cores for each ApplicationVM ) 2 ApplicationContainer

    Hacene & Marc
